ge. We also document substantial evidence of backdating =E2=80=93 investors=
 falsifying the date of their gift to capture a larger tax break. We show w=
hy lax reporting and enforcement encourage insider giving, explain why insi=
der giving represents a policy failure, and highlight the theoretical impli=
cations of these findings to broader corporate, securities, and tax debates=
.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The theory is roughly:</p><u=
